  "lemmas": {
    "OPEN": {
      "name": "OPEN_core_multimate_extension_and_ep_mark",
      "statement": "(1) At free_core = 846161, bound or eliminate multipads: core multi-mates of size m_c that share a CS e-extension into one j-fiber.\n(2) Inject free-1 CS e-set pairs into e\u00b7p labels (budget e\u00b7p = 143763024447376).\nCAS: Sage multipad examples; msolve on joint core+side systems.",
      "status": "OPEN"
    },
    "core_multimates": {
      "check_identity": true,
      "deployed_free_core": 846161,
      "deployed_m_c": 913632,
      "identity": "j - 2*w - 2 == m_c - w - 1",
      "name": "multipad_cores_are_depth_w_multimates",
      "proof": [
        "v21: deg(\u039b_C \u2212 \u039b_{C'}) \u2264 j\u22122w\u22122.",
        "j\u22122w\u22122 = (j\u2212w\u22121) \u2212 w \u2212 1 = m_c \u2212 w \u2212 1.",
        "For monic degree-m_c locators, deg(diff) \u2264 m_c\u2212w\u22121 is exactly the condition that the first w monic high coefficients agree, i.e. Phi_w(C)=Phi_w(C')."
      ],
      "statement": "Let e=w+1 and m_c = j\u2212e = j\u2212w\u22121. If C\u2260C' are m_c-subsets admitting a free-1 CS pair (U,V) of e-sets with Phi_w(C\u222aU)=Phi_w(C'\u222aU), then Phi_w(C)=Phi_w(C'). Equivalently, multipad cores are depth-w multi-mates of size m_c.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "ep_mark_negative": {
      "deployed_e_p": 143763024447376,
      "name": "ep_mark_candidates_collide",
      "proof": [
        "Toy census in toy_suite.ep_mark_bank.",
        "Budget: e\u00b7p = t\u00b7p deployed (t=e). Injection remains OPEN."
      ],
      "statement": "Natural free-1 CS ordered-pair marks of size \u2264 e\u00b7p \u2014 (minU mod e, c0U), (minU mod e, c0V), (minU mod e, \u0394c), (min(U\u222aV) mod e, c0U), (min(U\u222aV) mod e, \u0394c) \u2014 all collide on toy free-1 CS pairs, including when restricted to M_pad=1 side keys. No tested e\u00b7p-scale mark is injective on CS ordered pairs.",
      "status": "BANKED_NEGATIVE"
    },
    "free_core": {
      "deployed_free_core": 846161,
      "deployed_j_le_2w_plus_1": false,
      "name": "free_core_dictionary",
      "proof": [
        "m_c = j\u2212w\u22121; free_core = m_c\u2212w = j\u22122w\u22121.",
        "If m_c \u2264 w, Phi_w includes coefficients of X^{m_c\u22121},\u2026,X^{m_c\u2212w} which cover all of X^{m_c\u22121},\u2026,X^0 when w \u2265 m_c, so monic of degree m_c is unique given Phi_w. Multipad needs two cores with same Phi_w (previous lemma), impossible unless C=C'.",
        "Note j \u2264 2w+1 is equivalent to j < 2w+2 for integers, recovering v21."
      ],
      "statement": "Write free_core = m_c \u2212 w = j \u2212 2w \u2212 1. Then:\n  free_core \u2264 0  \u21d4  j \u2264 2w+1  \u21d4  m_c \u2264 w\n    \u21d2 monic degree-m_c locator is determined by Phi_w (w \u2265 m_c uses \u2265 all non-leading coeffs) \u21d2 at most one core per Phi_w value \u21d2 M_pad \u2264 1.\n  free_core = 1  \u21d4  j = 2w+2  \u21d2 cores free-1; CS packing applies.\n  free_core \u2265 1  \u21d4  j \u2265 2w+2 (deployed free_core = j\u22122w\u22121 \u226b 1).",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "path": {
      "name": "payment_path_restated",
      "proof": [
        "v20 bridge + free_core dictionary + deployed t=e."
      ],
      "statement": "A_SP \u2264 t\u00b7p if either:\n  (i)  M_pad\u22641 (e.g. free_core\u22640 / j\u22642w+1) and CS ordered pairs inject into e\u00b7p (=t\u00b7p=143763024447376 deployed), or\n  (ii) multipads controlled so N_ord \u2264 t\u00b7p by other means.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "reduction": {
      "name": "multipad_requires_core_multimates",
      "program": "Open core multi-mate control at (m_c,w) with free_core=j\u22122w\u22121, plus joint CS-extension constraint \u2014 stricter than raw M_m(m_c,w).",
      "proof": [
        "M_pad\u22652 means \u22652 cores for one side key (U,V) in fiber z.",
        "Previous lemma: those cores share Phi_w.",
        "They share the same CS (U,V) by construction of the side key."
      ],
      "statement": "M_pad(z) \u2265 2 only if there exist distinct m_c-subsets with the same depth-w prefix that both admit a common free-1 CS e-extension pair (U,V) lifting into fiber z. Thus controlling multipads reduces to controlling core multi-mates of size m_c at depth w that are jointly extendable by one CS side pair.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    }
  },
